Rows of highrises and skyscrapers combine to create a fascinating variance of texture and depth.

Pictured here is a panoramic aerial view of Manhattan from the One World Observatory in Lower Manhattan. Some neighborhoods that can be seen here are the East Village, the Lower East Side, Tribeca, and Union Square with the Empire State building in midtown and the east river in the far distance.

Riverside Park is a scenic waterfront public park in the Upper West Side, Morningside Heights, and Hamilton Heights neighborhoods of the borough of Manhattan in New York City. The park measures 4 miles (6.4 km) long and 100 to 500 feet (30 to 152 m) wide, running between the Hudson River and Henry Hudson Parkway to the west and the serpentine Riverside Drive to the east.

An aerial view of Tribeca and Civic Center neighborhoods of Lower Manhattan, New York City. The Two Bridges, Lower East Side, Chinatown neighborhoods in the distance. Some iconic buildings here include the Four Seasons Hotel, the Jacob K. Javits Federal Building, and 56 Leonard.

Pictured here is the view of Brooklyn's Cobble Hill, Columbia Street Waterfront District, Red Hook , and theGovernor's Island from the Financial District of Lower Manhattan, New York City, USA. The Hugh L. Carey Tunnel runs below the water pictured here. You will notice the Hugh L. Carey Tunnel Ventilation Building protruding next to the Governors Island.

A handwritten sign on the window of a closed restaurant in New York City announces its permanent closure after 22 years of service. The reflection of city buildings and a passerby adds depth to the image, capturing the emotional impact of businesses shutting down.
The lofty Olympia Dumbo was designed by New York-based Hill West Architects. This 33-story residential tower rises above New York Harbor and is the tallest building in Brooklyn's DUMBO neighborhood.
